<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The code casts away the const qualifier by passing a const char * (name) as a plain void *: return_code = OS_ObjectIdFindNextMatch(OS_ObjectNameMatch, (void *)name, token); This removes const-qualification and means the pointer passed does not point to a const-qualified type, violating the intent of Rule 8.13. Fix by changing the API to accept const void * (or const char *) or avoid the cast so the pointer remains const-qualified.
</scenario>

